---
description: Database and persistence rules for PostgreSQL-backed apps
globs:
  - "backend/app/models/**/*.py"
  - "backend/app/services/**/*.py"
  - "backend/alembic/**/*.py"
  - "backend/**/migrations/**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---
- Keep database models separate from API schemas.
- Do not hardcode database credentials or connection strings.
- Prefer migrations for schema changes.
- Consider existing data when changing columns, defaults, or constraints.
- Add indexes and constraints deliberately, not implicitly.
